caption: Nice open place with lots of room. The downside for me was when I was placing my order and what appears to be a manager or owner came up to our table and ask if I was done because the waiter was very busy and had a big party waiting for him. HOW RUDE! I did not take long asking for my food and was done when the manager approached us. Even if I did take long to order the correct thing would of been for the manager to ask if he could answer any questions and help the poor waiter who was clearly running endlessly back and forth. In either case the waiter was great. He handle rush hour dinner very well. If you have been to this place you know how big this place is and to run from one end to another takes great work. So the food.. We had burgers and fries and they were great no complaints. My child order the pasta with bolognese and it was okay, I had better. Overall the food was good and the ambience is nice. I think that if the manager or whoever that was would have not been rude I would of gave them 4 stars.

I've only been here for drinks in winter, so I can't speak to the food or outside space, though I certainly would try it out. I love how homey this place feels. It's set up like a mix between a garage/studio/cabin living room, with artwork, knick knacks, and old furniture everywhere.  The bar could be a bit bigger for a space this size — it's better sized for a single bartender as opposed to two. They definitely could use a little bit more elbow room. It was a bit hard to order a drink, especially as bar seating also served diners.  Overall, this is a great time for a small group of friends. It's not a dance joint, but more of a drink-and-catch-up spot. You can see each other, move around, and interact easily. The music is nothing special — benign enough that it just blends into the background.

I don't really know why I keep coming back here.  The food is actually really great, and live jazz is good as well, but aside from that, 4 out of 5 times I have a pretty bad experience.  The service is really slow -- I've waited over an hour for food at least 2 or 3 times and I've sat at the bar for 10+ minutes before the bartender acknowledged me -- and often unfriendly or incompetent. Several times I've had wrong items on my bill.  Once I had to tell the bartender he did his math wrong and shorted me $5 in change.  Most recently we showed up around 8pm, ordered some food and some wine and after an hour were told there was a health inspection going on and they didn't know when our food would be start being prepared.  I know you can't really help a health inspection, but it would have been nice to have been told that BEFORE we waited for an hour.  The bartender said our food would be on the house, but by then it was after 9pm and we were starving.  He comped one round of drinks, which was nice, but he wasn't very apologetic about it and said "good luck" to us when we left.  Maybe he didn't intend to be rude, but it sure came across that way.  Unfortunately they won't serve food on the patio (I was told it was because they allow smoking and dogs out there, but that's confusing to me because there are tons of other restaurants that also allow this on their patio and still serve food -- maybe those other places are breaking the law?)  tl;dr: food & jazz is great, but be ready for terrible service.
